ss": "", "is_removed": false, "media": {"resized_resolutions": [{"reference": "/scale/mjSty6r72OEDOmFC.jpeg", "width": 768, "content-type": "jpeg", "height": 768}], "blurhash": "UBCsdOD+E4adkvt6kCxt9cf9%0t6%FNJRjWB", "full_resolution": [896, 896]}, "title": "Take time to play outside.  Touch grass.  If you can't find any I know a guy with jars of grass you could touch.  ", "last_comment_created": 1778468492931, "content": "", "score_down": 0, "author_flair_text": "", "pro_tier": 0, "is_stickied": false, "is_nsfw": false, "is_deleted": false, "is_image": true, "comments": 3, "score_up": 79, "is_edited": false, "is_moderator": false, "awards": 0, "vote_state": 2, "link_metadata": {"status": 200}, "post_flair_text": "", "archive_id": ""}, {"is_locked": false, "tweet_id": "", "sticky_comment": 0, "is_video_mp4": false, "type": "text", "uuid": "1ASsPjheqZ", "is_twitter": false, "is_admin": false, "score": 91, "suggested_sort": 0, "post_flair_class": "", "id": 8611283, "raw_content": "https://x.com/OunkaOnX/status/2052595571102543966\nNothing against Jews or Israel per se.\n\nBut the fact that Israel supporters have pushed Trump into war in the middle east, even though he knows the people pushing it hate him is infuriating.\n\nI will never stop supporting Trump. The man took a bullet for us. But the fact that he couldn't directly justify the war to Tucker, who has publicly supported him and his messaging, suggests that it's a compromise. Something Trump feels he has to do for reasons he can't specify. Maybe it's to keep his donors on side for the midterms. Maybe it's for Vance's run. Or maybe he's been threatened.\n\nTurning against Trump only fractures MAGA and empowers the adversary. Tucker should know better. \n\nInstead, we should focus on picking off the imposters, the disloyal MIGA agents on Capitol Hill.  I think John Thune needs to learn a lesson.", "author": "SuperDuperBasedMD", "created": 1778461604963, "profile_picture": "", "community": "TheDonald", "ad_tier": 2, "last_comment_author": "WeWillRideAgain", "is_video": false, "video_link": "", "is_new_user": false, "domain": "", "is_crosspost": false, "preview": "", "removal_source": "", "link": "", "author_flair_class": "", "is_removed": false, "media": {"resized_resolutions": [], "blurhash": "", "full_resolution": []}, "title": "The Israeli Deep State and its slave the Israel First Lobby need to be destroyed", "last_comment_created": 1778495881175, "content": "<p><a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://x.com/OunkaOnX/status/2052595571102543966\" target=\"_blank\">https://x.com/OunkaOnX/status/2052595571102543966</a>\nNothing against Jews or Israel per se.</p>\n<p>But the fact that Israel supporters have pushed Trump into war in the middle east, even though he knows the people pushing it hate him is infuriating.</p>\n<p>I will never stop supporting Trump. The man took a bullet for us. But the fact that he couldn't directly justify the war to Tucker, who has publicly supported him and his messaging, suggests that it's a compromise. Something Trump feels he has to do for reasons he can't specify. Maybe it's to keep his donors on side for the midterms. Maybe it's for Vance's run. Or maybe he's been threatened.</p>\n<p>Turning against Trump only fractures MAGA and empowers the adversary. Tucker should know better.</p>\n<p>Instead, we should focus on picking off the imposters, the disloyal MIGA agents on Capitol Hill.  I think John Thune needs to learn a lesson.</p>\n", "score_down": 0, "author_flair_text": "", "pro_tier": 0, "is_stickied": false, "is_nsfw": false, "is_deleted": false, "is_image": false, "comments": 114, "score_up": 91, "is_edited": false, "is_moderator": false, "awards": 0, "vote_state": 2, "link_metadata": {"status": 200}, "post_flair_text": "", "archive_id": ""}, {"is_locked": false, "tweet_id": "2053550639238824142", "sticky_comment": 0, "is_video_mp4": false, "type": "link", "uuid": "1ASsPjiU3m", "is_twitter": true, "is_admin": false, "score": 29, "suggested_so